&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Consultant Clinical Psychologist - Band 8c&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Permanent, full-time 37.5 hours per week&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are looking for an experienced and resilient psychologist to lead our crisis and anxiety, depression, trauma and personality disorder pathways. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The candidate should be a pragmatic and creative practitioner who can demonstrate that they meet the needs people in crisis, often in a potentially chaotic inpatient environment. They should also have a track record in supporting and delivering a range of psychological therapy interventions from crisis to follow-up situations. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;We will look for experience in leadership of both psychological therapists and in supporting multi-disciplinary colleagues to undertake psychosocial interventions. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Y&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;ou will join a team of senior psychological therapists who offer services to older people, people experiencing psychosis, ASD and peri-natal issues.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Neil Springham&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Lead for Psychological Therapies&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: neil.springham@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number: 01689 892300&lt;/p&gt;
